      "writtenOn": "2019-06-11T16:37:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we can use _mm_packs_epi32() to make this easier?  The one tricky bit is that it converts i32 -\u003e i16, not u16, but that\u0027s pretty easy to work around by sign-extending the inputs as you isolate red and green anyway by using srai (Shift Right Arithmetic by Immediate):\n\n  *r \u003d _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_srai_epi32(_mm_slli_epi32(_0123, 16), 16),\n                       _mm_srai_epi32(_mm_slli_epi32(_4567, 16), 16));\n  *g \u003d _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_srai_epi32(_0123, 16),\n                       _mm_srai_epi32(_4567, 16));\n\nSSE4.1 and up do have _mm_packus_epi32() to translate i32 -\u003e u16, so you could technically cut one math instruction here by replacing the two shifts for red with an \u00260xffff, but I don\u0027t really see much downside to just using _mm_packs_epi32 across the board.",
      "revId": "e768502e812b2571002ea12c88e6056d10f88262",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
